The paper focuses on the use of vision-based tracking and identification for a team of humanoid robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Histogram of Oriented Gradients descriptor and multiclass classifier for detection and tracking involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The use of cost function and Hungarian algorithm for globally optimal labeling involves optimization and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the application of the system on a soccer field involves control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
